# CSS Styles

# There are three main ways that you can use CSS code: Inline, Internal and External.
Inline - by using the style attribute inside HTML elements. I.E. <h1 style="color:blue;">A Blue Heading</h1>
Internal - by using a <style> element in the <head> section. I>E. body {background-color: powderblue;}
External - by using a <link> element to link to an external CSS file. I.E. <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">







